File: The Old Mutual group board says trust between CEO Peter Moyo and the board has broken down. JOHANNESBURG - Old Mutual has suspended its CEO Peter Moyo. In an update to shareholders, the Old Mutual group board says trust between him and the board has broken down. Moyo headed both Old Mutual Limited and Old Mutual Life Assurance Company Limited. READ: Old Mutual unveils multi-billion share buyback plan The company hasn’t given any other detail. Chief operating officer Iain Williamson will act as CEO for now.